        <h2 class="text_header">Something Kool</h2>
        <p class="text_para">What I think is really interesting and am proud of is the authentication Linkage has. I used the Devise Ruby gem for aunthentication. Users can sign up and sign in. Only users who sign up can create posts. With the authentication, the postgres database stores all of the users data and assigns the user an id. Only the user who created the post can go in and choose to edit or delete the post due to having the same id. </p>
